headline: Qualcomm (QCOM) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
summary: Cristiano Renno Amon: Thank you, Mauricio.  QCT revenues of $9.8 billion, up 9% sequentially, were driven by strong end customer demand for Snapdragon-powered premium tier Android handsets, continued demand for automotive Snapdragon digital chassis, and strength in IoT across industrial, Wi-Fi 7 access points, 5G fixed wireless, and smart glasses.  In addition, all three QCT revenue streams exceeded our expectations, including record automotive quarterly revenues in excess of $1 billion.

content.title: Qualcomm (QCOM) Q4 2025 Earnings Call Transcript
content.summary: Cristiano Renno Amon: Thank you, Mauricio.  QCT revenues of $9.8 billion, up 9% sequentially, were driven by strong end customer demand for Snapdragon-powered premium tier Android handsets, continued demand for automotive Snapdragon digital chassis, and strength in IoT across industrial, Wi-Fi 7 access points, 5G fixed wireless, and smart glasses.  In addition, all three QCT revenue streams exceeded our expectations, including record automotive quarterly revenues in excess of $1 billion.
